The paper deals with algorithmic solutions for the Pickup and Delivery Problem (PDP) in Euclidean Space, which is a classic problem in computer science. The paper proposes a polynomial time asymptotically optimal algorithm for vehicles with capacity $o(\sqrt[2d]{n})$ for the PDP, which is a problem in the domain of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also extends the algorithm to the classical single-vehicle PDP, which involves optimization and decision-making, and hence falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also deals with the problem of minimizing the Euclidean distance traveled by the vehicles, which is a problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.SI).
